Learned:
    1. When jets comne back with:
        Error: Can't find a root directory while resolving a config file path.

        it means it cannot find a config file.

        Solution: Add the --config option as per below.
        jest --config jest.unit.config.js ./src/core/domain/types.unit.test.ts


    2. jest TS loop through a set of non-arrays in a test that expects arrays
         Ex.1 :
         import { TestNonArray } from './unit-test-helpers';

         it.each<TestNonArray>(badArgsNonArray)(
            'should throw if sink not valid array',
            (badArray) => {
              expect(() => createMessageStoreWithWriteSink(badArray)).toThrow(
                'Sink must be an array'
              );
          });


          Ex. 2:
          export type TestNonString = (
            | number
            | null
            | undefined
            | Symbol
            | NullFunction
            | object
          )[];

          const badArgsNonString: ReadonlyArray<TestNonString> = [
              [null],
              [undefined],
              [0],
              [() => ({} as NullFunctionResult)],
              [{ a: 1 }],
              [Symbol('cucu')],
            ];

            it.each<TestNonArray>(badArgsNonString)(
                'should throw if param not a string',
                (nonString) => {
                  expect(() => emailIsValid(nonString)).toThrow();
                }
              );

    3. Learned how to produce an EmailAddress type in TS:
        see "Types.ts", function emailIsValid()